library(purrr)
total_data <- data.frame()
for (i in movie_names){
  tryCatch({
    
  # Scrape movie script
  url_script <- glue::glue("https://imsdb.com/scripts/{i}.html")
  data_read <- read_html(url_script)
  td <- data_read %>% html_elements("td")
  
  script <- td[which(grepl("<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td class=\"scrtext\">", td))] %>% 
    html_table() %>% 
    `[[`(1)

  script <- script[1,1]

  # Scrape movie genres
  j <- gsub(pattern = '-', replacement = '%20', i)
  url_genre <- glue::glue('https://imsdb.com/Movie%20Scripts/{j}%20Script.html')
  data_read_genre <- read_html(url_genre)
  elements_genre <- data_read_genre %>% 
  html_elements("a")

  elements_genre <- elements_genre[which(grepl("href=\"/genre/", elements_genre))]
  
  elements_genre <- elements_genre[which(grepl("title=", elements_genre))]
  
  elements_genre <- elements_genre %>% 
                  map(html_attrs) %>% 
                  map_df(~as.list(.))

  genres_list <- str_match(elements_genre$href, "/genre/([A-z-]+)")[,2]
  
  for (k in 1:length(genres_list)){
    nam <- paste("entry", k, sep = "")
    assign(nam, cbind(script, genres_list[k]))
  }
  
  # Combine script and genres
  data_combine <- do.call(rbind, lapply(paste0("entry", 1:length(genres_list)), get))
  total_data <- rbind(total_data, data_combine)
  
  }, error=function(e){})
}

  pred_prob <- rbind(pred_prob, colnames(result)[result[i] %in% -prob[i,]])

result_check <- cbind(result[,1:2], pred_prob)

  }

tuning_result <- data.frame()
j <- 0
for (k in seq(0.01, 0.3, 0.01)){
  learner <- lrn("classif.xgboost", nthread = 7, eta = k, nrounds = 100)

  learner$predict_type = 'prob'
  
  learner$train(script_task, row_ids = train_set)
    
  prediction <- learner$predict(script_task, row_ids = test_set)
  
  # Check prediction accuracy
  result <- as.data.table(prediction)
  
  prob <- t(apply(result[,-c(1:3)], 1, function(x) head(sort(-x), 3)))
  
  pred_prob <- data.frame()
  
  for (i in 1:nrow(result)){
    pred_prob <- rbind(pred_prob, colnames(result)[result[i] %in% -prob[i,]])
  }
  
  colnames(pred_prob) <- c('predGenre1', 'predGenre2', 'predGenre3')
  
  pred_prob <- apply(pred_prob, 2, function(x) gsub(pattern = '(prob.)([A-z]+)', replacement = '\\2', x))
  
  result_check <- cbind(result[,1:2], pred_prob)
  
  result_check$correctPred <- 0
  for (i in 1:nrow(result_check)){
    if (result_check$truth[i] %in% result_check[i, 3:5]){
      result_check$correctPred[i] <- 1
    }
  }
  
  # Final accuracy
  tuning_result <- rbind(tuning_result, sum(result_check$correctPred) / nrow(result_check))
  
  j <- j + 1
  
  tuning_result$eta[j] <- k
}

script_task <- TaskClassif$new(id = "text", backend = model_data, target = "genre")
script_task

## * Properties: multiclass
## * Features (10):
##   - dbl (10): topic_1, topic_10, topic_2, topic_3, topic_4, topic_5,
##     topic_6, topic_7, topic_8, topic_9
train_set <- 1:(nrow(model_data)-1)
test_set <- nrow(model_data)

# Final model
learner <- lrn("classif.xgboost", nthread = 7, eta = 0.22, nrounds = 100, min_child_weight = 1.4, gamma = 4, subsample = 0.21)

newMovie <- read.csv('thedarkknight-screenplay.csv')

colnames(newMovie)[1] <- 'text'

newMovie <- str_c(newMovie, collapse = " ")

newMovie <- cbind(newMovie, 'Crime')

colnames(newMovie) <- c('text', 'genre')

total_data <- rbind(total_data, newMovie)

# Clean text
Encoding(total_data$text) <- "UTF-8"

total_data$text[nrow(total_data)] <- total_data$text[nrow(total_data)] %>% 
  textclean::replace_contraction() %>% 
  str_replace_all(., "\n", " ") %>% 
  str_replace_all(., "(\\[.*?\\])", "") %>% 
  str_squish() %>% 
  gsub("([a-z])([A-Z])", "\\1 \\2", .) %>% 
  tolower() %>% 
  textstem::lemmatize_strings(.)

newScriptText = textProcessor(documents = total_data$text[nrow(total_data)], 
                          metadata = total_data[nrow(total_data),], 
                          stem = FALSE)
## Building corpus... 
## Converting to Lower Case... 
## Removing punctuation... 
## Removing stopwords... 
## Removing numbers... 
## Creating Output...
newScriptCorp = alignCorpus(new = newScriptText, old.vocab = topics10$vocab)
## Your new corpus now has 1 documents, 2584 non-zero terms of 2770 total terms in the original set. 
## 186 terms from the new data did not match.
## This means the new data contained 9.7% of the old terms
## and the old data contained 93.3% of the unique terms in the new data. 
## You have retained 16717 tokens of the 17429 tokens you started with (95.9%).
newScriptFitted = fitNewDocuments(model = topics10, documents = newScriptCorp$documents, 
                newData = newScriptCorp$meta, origData = scirpt_prep$meta)
## .
newScript <- cbind(newScriptFitted$theta, total_data[nrow(total_data), 'genre'])
colnames(newScript) <- c(paste0("topic_", 1:10), "genre")
model_data <- rbind(model_data, newScript)
